Johannesburg- Former Finance minister, Tito Mboweni, has bowed out as a public servant. This comes after the former minister submitted his resignation as a member of parliament (MP) in the National Assembly today. Mboweni handed his resignation to the Speaker of parliament Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula, and it will be effective from the 31st of January 2022. The minister tweeted that the journey was long and sometimes lonely.  To read more political news and views, click here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.